Package org.svvrl.goal.core.util

Class PrioritySet<T>

java.lang.Object
org.svvrl.goal.core.util.PrioritySet<T>
Type Parameters:
T - the type of elements in the set
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<T>
public class PrioritySet<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<T>
A priority set is a set of elements with priorities. If two elements have the same priority, they can be compared by a comparator. Otherwise, their string representations will be compared instead.
Author:
Ming-Hsien Tsai
